  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nYou're helping program an emergency response robot for your school. The robot already has functions to sound an alarm and lock the doors, but now it needs an upgrade. You'll create a full emergency protocol that calls multiple safety steps in the right order, including a new function to secure the server room.\r\n\r\n1. Three safety functions are already defined for you:\r\n\r\n   * `sound_alarm()`\r\n   \r\n   * `lock_doors()`\r\n   \r\n   * `secure_server_room()`\r\n\r\n2. Write a new function called `emergency_protocol()` that:\r\n\r\n   * Calls `sound_alarm()` **twice** at the start (to make sure everyone hears it)\r\n   \r\n   * Then calls `lock_doors()`\r\n   \r\n   * Then calls `secure_server_room()`\r\n\r\n3. After defining `emergency_protocol()`, call it to run the full safety sequence.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nFunctions can call other functions—just make sure the ones you're calling are defined first!",
